The '''common jery''' ('''''Neomixis tenella''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Cisticolidae]].
It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Madagascar]].

Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical dry forest]] and [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]].

It was first described in 1866 by [[Gustav Hartlaub]].

